runs.comm: tossed up on a good length just outside off, Warner prefers to stay back and tuck it away towards midwicket
nips away outside off and cuts a flatter delivery coming in on middle, nicely worked from Warner
flighted on middle and leg, Warner keeps it out
runs at the bowler and plays around a reasonably straight delivery. Kisses the back pad, beats the keeper who was rather blinded. Still might be a chance missed. Raza is very displeased
goes back to a shortish delivery and cuts it, if a little uppishly, towards point

oopsy, Afridi dives a little lazily and Finch treats himself to a one-handed boundary. Even he stares at it with a little bit of surprise. It was full on middle and off stump, Finch was into the flick a little too early and checked his shot. But the timing he mustered was quite staggering
back of a length and outside off at 148 kph, Finch looks to punch through the covers and is beaten soundly
146 kph, jumps back in his crease to try an pull a delivery that is not quite short enough. Mistimes it to square leg
that's lovely. Slants a good length ball across Finch and gets a little nip away to help himself. Beats Finch a second time in the over
goes for another pull as he misjudges the length again. Irfan gets the ball to lift up off just back of a length and this one thuds into Finch's stomach. Gets an earful from Irfan
pull again, his front leg comes off the turf to help him control it. Kept down to deep square leg
tossed up on off stump, Finch is forward to block solidly
fired it in a decent clip. Finch goes back and tries to cut, but this ball has skid on into the keeper's gloves. Didn't miss the leg stump by much either

goes for a sweep, but he hasn't controlled it properly. "Catch it," everyone cries and Mohammad Irfan at short fine leg does not disappoint. Dubai is up and buzzing. A top edge removes the Australia captain
pushes it through again and Maxi goes back to push into the covers
a hint of turn off a fuller ball on off stump, Maxi defends with an open face at the last minute
he's switched it! When the orthodox strokes don't work, pull out a left-handed sweep and send the length ball sailing away to the square leg/ third man boundary

that's been carved over the off side field. Nipped down the track, but Irfan pulled his length back. Didn't matter though as he has just enough room to imbue all his power into the stroke. Wins a staring contest with Irfan. Boy!
whipped away, there's no trouble with Warner's timing tonight. This was short and angled into the body, midwicket has a task on his hands
runs at Irfan, makes room and slashes at the slower ball. Fools Maxwell as he slashes a little too early and gets a thick outside edge. It flies over the lone slip fielder
moves away and flings down a yorker at 145 kph, Maxi tries to slice it to third man but isn't able to connect
waits on this shortish delivery and steers it behind point. Raza at deep third man is not quite quick enough to stop two. That's ordinary work
another top edge. He keeps making room to Irfan and for a third time he isn't able to hit where he intended. This short ball hurries onto him and takes the top edge to sail away
pushed through on middle and leg, Warner pushes it towards mid-on
loads up for a pull, but this shorter ball hugs the ground. No pace on the ball also plays its part as he inside edges
worked away square on the leg side as Raza begins to dart it in
length, fast, on leg stump. Maxi made room and swung free. But this outfield is quite sluggish. It was so in the first innings as well. Three runs

this was sort of the stroke Awais Zia fell to. Backed away and tried to slice it over the extra cover region. Warner though has a little more pace to work with and that comes to his aid has he powers the ball to the off side boundary
flatter, quicker and fired in on leg stump. These boundaries are getting to Raza. Nudged behind square leg
goes for a reverse swat, but it was slid too quickly down the leg side for Maxi.

Welcome back, Star Man. Although this one isn't quite stationary. This time the quicker ball does the batsman. It came in off the deck to catch Maxi, who was possibly hoping to cut a length ball away, napping. The adjustment to hit down the ground isn't quick enough. Struck on the knee-roll and in front of off stump.
gets a little off line with a length ball and slides it down the leg side
a little flight outside off, he nudges down the pitch and blocks
another little trip down the pitch and this time he is able to work the good length ball through midwicket
switches around the wicket and gets a good length ball to turn in quite sharply to Warner. Struck on the pads
stays back to a fuller ball and blocks it, rather gingerly
flighted just outside off, Smith pushes it to the left of short cover
gets down the track and whips the flighted ball behind square leg. Irfan tracks the ball down and puts a boot down on it. But that allows him to get a couple
flighted on middle and off, Smith leans forward into a defensive push

ooohh, another one! Pakistan are making a fist of this. Smith is livid at affording them the opportunity. He ran down the track and went for another whip, this time in front of the wicket. Wahab, at mid-on, takes a couple of steps to his left, dives and holds on to an important catch
flighted outside off, Hughes plays around his front pad towards short fine leg
was caught between flicking and sweeping and ends up scooping the ball behind square leg. "Catch it," they cry but it lands safely. Good pressure being kept up
this one doesn't turn as Afridi continues around the wicket. Was preparing to work it with the turn into the on side then he has to adjust with a late cut and misses
offers up a half-volley and Hughes is forward and slaps the ball through the covers
this fuller ball does turn and he loads up for the sweep, doesn't connect. Appeal from Afridi but the batsman had made himself go outside off
102 kph, fired in full but Hughes was waiting for it with a sweep
tossed up slower on off stump, defended carefully
flighted outside off, Warner is happy with a checked drive to the left of cover
Warner certainly loves it. Its a length ball from Wahab and it's been smacked straight down the ground. Watches the ball sail over long-off quite casually
change of pace, Warner picks it and turns it away behind square leg.
fishes outside off. Nobody home. Lovely bowling as he gets a back of a length delivery to nip away. Hughes plays a nothing stroke, pushing an angled face at it. With slips lying in wait
goes for a pull, it's not short enough for the pull and he was dragging it from a shade outside off as well. It sails up into the Dubai sky. Sohaib Maqsood runs to his right from slip and holds on!
back of a length and on off stump, Warner blocks under his eyes
banged in short, Warner sways away from it and lets it through to the keeper. Absorbs a typical angry fast-bowler's stare from Wahab
flighted on middle, Faulkner pushes it down the ground. Not all that comfortably
takes advantage of a flighted ball on the pads and turns it away through square leg

lured him into a drive away from the body. This is very good bowling from Pakistan. They're keeping things tight. They're coaxing mistakes, like this. Off a flighted ball, Warner plays a lazy drive but it falls short of point
this is shorter and coming in at him, backs away and cuts through cover
feigns to make room, but he stays put. Afridi is not fooled as he fllights it in on middle. Warner whips it to mid-on
another loopy ball on off stump, Warner waits for a touch more this time and drills it to the right of the cover fielder
lets a back of a length delivery come in and taps it into the point region. Sets off but Shehzad is too quick at point
inside edge! He's working up some pace here. Faulker's prod off the front foot sneaks away to fine leg
that's a smashing shot! Moves away outside leg, benefits from the bowler pitching short and creams it through point. Too good
fires this in full and on leg stump, Warner though is capably behind it and pushes to long-on
banged in short, Faulkner is deep in his crease and has to leap up to get on top of the ball. Tucks it into the vacant midwicket region.

that's a slower ball, Warner realises it and taps it down the ground. Neatly done, but as soon as he's at the other end, he pulls his helmet off and is inspecting his left eye. Asks for help from the dressing room. Gets some drops
poor ball to start and Warner tucks into it. Pulls a long hop to long-on
good length ball on off stump, holds in and turns away to surprise Faulker. Catches him between a punch and a defensive push
tossed up outside off, Faulkner drives it through the covers a little uppishly
jumps back in his crease and pounces on a short ball on middle with glee. He's taking control of the chase
slog sweep! This seems to be the wrong 'un from Nasim but Warner doesn't care. He sees it tossed up. it is an opportunity to belt the ball away and belt he does
tossed up outside off, safely defended to end the over
pushed through on leg stump, Faulker works it into the midwicket region
good length ball with a little turn on off stump, Faulker goes back and taps it to mid-on
flighted on off stump, Faulker is forward to block
slower and tossed up on leg stump, Faulker works it away behind square leg. No need to take any risks
sees the ball short and gets down one one knee to half-pull and half-sweep it away behind square leg. Mohammad Irfan running from fine leg pulls out a slide and is able to make the save
another shorter ball, another sweep/ pull from Warner. Irfan gets into the act again
whoa, he was making room and the offspinner gripping the pitch and turning away almost beat him. Warner reaches out as much as he can and toe ends it to deep point.
goes back to a good length ball and defends
gets back to a shortish ball on middle and mistimes a pull down the ground
tossed up on off stump, Faulker nudges it through square leg. But the umpire calls a no-ball. Maqsood oversteps and presents a free hit

tonk it over midwicket while becoming temporarily right-handed. There really was no risk here, so he jumps around and pummels it over midwicket. Rocks his bat like a cradle to celebrate. He did become a father recently
tossed up on middle and leg, turned away through midwicket.
miscalculations galore as Masood bowls, Faulker pushes down the ground past mid-off. This single does close out the game though.
